# Security Rules (V2.1)

**Authority:** `00_architecture_authority.mdc` · **Detail:** `doc/ARCHITECTURE_V2_AGENT_RULES.md`

## Authentication

| Concern | Implementation |
|---------|----------------|
| Tenant API JWT | `authMiddleware` on `/api/v1` |
| Request context | `req.tenantId`, `req.userId`, `req.role` on `AuthedRequest` |
| Admin portal | `/api/admin` — separate JWT via `adminPortal/`, not tenant-scoped |
| MFA | `shared/rbac/mfaPolicy.ts` → `backend/src/auth/mfaPolicy.ts` |
| Sessions | `modules/auth/` — `UserSessionRepository`, `MfaRepository` |
| Password policy | `backend/src/utils/passwordPolicy.ts` |

## Tenant isolation (critical)

- **Never** authorize using `tenant_id` from request body, query string, or client headers
- Always use `req.tenantId` set by `authMiddleware` after JWT verification
- Repository queries: `WHERE tenant_id = $1` with constructor `tenantId`
- Socket: join only `tenant:${tenantId}`; clients filter foreign `tenantId` in payloads
- PostgreSQL RLS is **deferred** (post-launch P5) — application-layer scoping is mandatory today

## Secrets & configuration

- **Never** commit `.env`, `.env.staging`, `.env.production`, tokens, keys, `.pfx`
- Production env validation: `backend/src/utils/productionEnvCheck.ts`
- Use env examples: `.env.staging.example`, `.env.production.example`

## API hardening

- Rate limiting on public endpoints (login, lookup) — `express-rate-limit`
- `sendFailure(res, 400, 'CODE', 'message')` — never expose SQL or stack traces
- `handleRouteError` logs server-side; client gets safe message
- Webhooks: verify signatures (Paddle, WhatsApp) before processing

## Documents & files

- Store files in R2 via `DocumentStorageService`
- Metadata in `document_metadata` (tenant-scoped)
- **No** new inline `file_data` BLOB columns
- Legacy `documents` table: read-only archive

## Subscription & license

- `requireActiveSubscription()` on tenant `/api/v1` stack
- Billing/license enforcement in `modules/billing/`

## Audit & privacy

- Tenant mutations: `recordDomainMutation()` / `withAudit()`
- Privacy requests: `modules/privacy/`
- Enterprise audit: `modules/organization/services/enterpriseAuditService.ts`

## Electron / desktop

- API client connects to configured host (staging 3001 / production 3000)
- No local SQLite credential storage for business data

## MUST NOT

- Client-supplied tenant override
- Cross-tenant socket broadcasts
- Log passwords, JWTs, or full PII in production
- Skip auth middleware on tenant business routes
- Store secrets in source code or committed config

## Security review triggers

New code requires extra care when touching:

- Auth flows, password reset, MFA
- Admin portal routes
- Webhook ingress
- Backup restore / DR
- Cross-tenant admin queries
